ISSUE 1 — DASHBOARD SHOWING INCORRECT / HARDCODED VALUES
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

ROOT CAUSE:
  - /auth/achievements returns same done_pct for all 4 macros
    (kcal_pct, protein_pct, carbs_pct, fat_pct)
  - /api/dashboard returns hardcoded plans:[], streak:0 always
  - dashboard.html JS does not read individual macro values

FILES TO CHANGE:
  1. backend/routes/auth.py  →  achievements() function
  2. backend/routes/main.py  →  dashboard() function
  3. pages/dashboard.html    →  JS fetch + chart rendering

EXACT FIXES:

  [auth.py – achievements()]
  - Map each check key in weekly plan to its macro category:
      breakfast checks  → carbs_pct  (energy/carb-heavy meals)
      lunch checks      → protein_pct
      dinner checks     → fat_pct
      overall done days → kcal_pct
  - Calculate each percentage independently:
      kcal_pct    = (days_with_any_meal_done / 7) * 100
      protein_pct = (lunch_checks_ticked / total_lunch_checks) * 100
      carbs_pct   = (breakfast_checks_ticked / total_breakfast) * 100
      fat_pct     = (dinner_checks_ticked / total_dinner) * 100
  - weekly_data[] must reflect per-day completion % (already correct)
  - Return real profile values, not fallback defaults when profile exists

  [main.py – dashboard()]
  - Import WeeklyPlan, UserProfile models
  - Call the same logic as achievements() — do NOT duplicate, import helper
  - Return real streak count (consecutive done days from Sunday backwards)
  - Return real plans list from weekly_plan.plan_json

  [dashboard.html – JS]
  - Read response.kcal_pct, protein_pct, carbs_pct, fat_pct separately
  - Update each progress ring with its own value
  - Update each bar in the weekly bar chart with weekly_data[i]
  - Show real kcal / protein / carbs / fat targets from response
  - Display done_days list as badges or checkmarks on day labels


