ISSUE 4 — AUTH FLOW INCOMPLETE (LOGIN / REGISTER / LOGOUT)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

ROOT CAUSE:
  - After login success, no redirect happens
  - After OTP verify, no redirect to correct next page
  - Logout button does not call /auth/logout API
  - Already-logged-in users can still visit login/register pages

FILES TO CHANGE:
  1. pages/login.html
  2. pages/register.html
  3. src/auth-header.js

EXACT FIXES:

  [login.html]
  - On page load: fetch GET /auth/me
      → if 200 (already logged in): redirect to /pages/home.html
  - POST /auth/login on form submit:
      → on success (200): redirect to /pages/home.html
      → on 403 (unverified): show OTP input step, don't redirect yet
      → on 401: show "Incorrect email/phone or password."
  - All fetch calls must use relative URL /auth/login (not localhost)
  - Include credentials: 'include' in all fetch calls

  [register.html]
  - On page load: fetch GET /auth/me
      → if 200 (already logged in): redirect to /pages/home.html
  - After POST /auth/register/email or /auth/register/phone succeeds:
      → show OTP step / OTP input field
      → auto-fill OTP if dev_otp present in response (see Issue 2)
  - After POST /auth/verify/email or /auth/verify/phone succeeds:
      → fetch GET /auth/profile to check if profile exists
      → if no profile: redirect to /pages/body-needs.html
      → if profile exists: redirect to /pages/home.html

  [auth-header.js]
  - Must be included in every protected page via <script src="/src/auth-header.js">
  - On load: fetch GET /auth/me with credentials:'include'
      → if 401: redirect to /pages/login.html
      → if ok: populate header username element with user.username or email
  - Logout button (id="logout-btn") click handler:
      → POST /auth/logout with credentials:'include'
      → on success: redirect to /pages/login.html
  - Nav links must be dynamically set to correct /pages/* paths


